orischer Medialität und zur Frage nach dem Potenzial von Geschichtsdingen sie eröffnen können.  afunded by Universität Bielefeld  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 4aBielefeld University Press. 4aErinnerungskultur. 4aFigur. 4aGeschichte. 4aKulturgeschichte. 4aKunst. 4aKunstgeschichte. 4aMaterielle Kultur. 4aMuseum. 4aPferd. 4aPferdfiguren. 4aPraktische Museumskunde. 4aReinhart Koselleck. 4aReiter. 4aUniversitätssammlung. 7aHISTORY / Social History.2bisacsh  aArt History.  aArt.  aBielefeld University Press.  aCultural History.  aFigure.  aHistory.  aHorse Figures.  aHorse.  aHorseman.  aMaterial Culture.  aMemory Culture.  aMuseum.  aPractical Museography.  aReinhart Koselleck.  aUniversity Collection.1 aBlume, Judith, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrandt, Bettina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDunkhase, Jan Eike, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHochkirchen, Britta, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKoselleck, Felicitas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKoselleck, Katharina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKoselleck, Ruppe, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLink, Sarah Elena, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRegazzoni, Lisa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRegazzoni, Lisa, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aTacke, Charlotte, econtributor.4ctb4http